{{Short description|Shinto shrine in Osaka Prefecture, Japan}} {{Infobox religious building | name = {{nihongo|Tamatsukuri Inari Shrine|玉造稲荷神社|Tamatsukuri-Inari-jinja}} | image = Tamatsukuri-inari-jinja haiden.jpeg | caption = Tamatsukuri Inari Shrine's ''[[haiden (Shinto)|haiden]]'' | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|34|40|41|N|135|31|48|E|region:JP_source:kolossus-jawiki|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} '''{{nihongo|Tamatsukuri Inari Shrine|玉造稲荷神社|Tamatsukuri-Inari-jinja}}''' is a shrine dedicated to the [[Shinto]] ''[[kami]]'' ('god') [[Inari (mythology)|Inari]]. Its construction can be traced to 12 BCE, and Inari was enshrined there by [[Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] in the 1580s to protect [[Osaka Castle]].<ref>[http://www.tourism.city.osaka.jp/en/search_osaka/reference/sights.php Osaka Visitor's Guide]</ref>
==Location==
The shrine is a short walk north from exit #1 of the Tamatsukuri Station on the Nagahori-tsurumi-ryokuchi Line of the [[Osaka]] subway system. It is close to the [[Japan Railways|JR]] Loop Line.
The address is 2-3-8, Tamatsukuri, Chūō-ku, Osaka City, 540-0004.
==References== {{Reflist}}
==External links== {{Commons category|Tamatsukuri-inari-jinja}} Website (Japanese): [http://www.inari.or.jp www.inari.or.jp]
{{Shinto shrine}} {{Authority control}}
